**Stats:** 3 exchanges = 18 lines (6 lines per exchange)

### Current Implementation

**File:** `src/modules/conversationLogger.ts`

**Line 133 - Header:**
```typescript
const header = `Say What Want\n${'='.repeat(50)}\n\n`;
```

**Lines 78-86 - Message format:**
```typescript
formatMessage(username: string, text: string, timestamp: number): string {
  const dateStr = new Date(timestamp).toLocaleString();
  const sanitizedText = text
    .replace(/\0/g, '')
    .replace(/[\x00-\x08\x0B-\x0C\x0E-\x1F\x7F]/g, '');
  
  return `${username} (${dateStr}):\n${sanitizedText}`;
}
```

**Line 124 - Assembly:**
```typescript
const newContent = `${humanEntry}\n\n${aiEntry}\n\n`;
```

### Problems

1. **Repetitive timestamps** - Full date/time on every message
2. **Verbose usernames** - Full name repeated endlessly
3. **Generic header** - No AI entity name, no start time
4. **Hard to scan** - 60-exchange = 360+ lines

